! Knowledge Management Research

!! Definition
Knowledge Management (KM) is the process of creating, sharing, using and managing the knowledge and information of an organization or individual.

!! Personal Knowledge Management (PKM)
PKM focuses on individual knowledge workers and their personal information management strategies.

!!! Core Activities
* ''Capture'': Recording information and ideas
* ''Organize'': Structuring and categorizing knowledge
* ''Process'': Analyzing and synthesizing information
* ''Connect'': Linking related concepts
* ''Share'': Disseminating knowledge

!! Tools and Techniques

!!! Digital Tools
* [[TiddlyWiki]] - Non-linear personal wiki
* Obsidian - Graph-based note-taking
* Notion - All-in-one workspace
* Roam Research - Bi-directional linking

!!! Methodologies
* Zettelkasten method
* PARA method (Projects, Areas, Resources, Archives)
* GTD (Getting Things Done)
* Mind mapping

!! AI Enhancement Opportunities
* Automated tagging and categorization
* Content summarization
* Relationship discovery
* Knowledge gap identification
* Smart search and retrieval

